<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><meta charset="utf-8" />
<title>CSS Transitions Test: transition-property - line-height</title>
<link href="http://www.intel.com" rel="author" title="Intel" />
<link href="mailto:shiyoux.tan@intel.com" rel="author" title="Shiyou Tan" />
<link href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-transitions/#animatable-css" rel="help" title="7.1. Properties from CSS" />
<meta content="interact" name="flags" />
<meta content="Test checks that the 'line-height' property is animatable." name="assert" />
<style>
  #test {
    line-height: 10px;
    transition-duration: 4s;
    transition-property: line-height;
    transition-timing-function: linear;
  }
</style>
</head><body>
  <p>Click the 'FillerText' below. Test passes if the 'FillerText' moves down gradually not immediately until it stops.</p>
  <div id="test">FillerTextFillerText</div>
  <script>
    (function() {
      var test = document.querySelector("#test");
      test.addEventListener("click", function(evt) {
        test.setAttribute("style", "line-height: 100px;");
      }, false);
    })();
  </script>

</body></html>